Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We are overjoyed that you are\Namong the millions around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.76,0:00:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who are viewing this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,An infirm Bible student named Joyce,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who lives in Southeast Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed her appreciation\Nfor these arrangements by saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.10,0:00:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“With the convention being streamed online,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.73,0:00:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“I don’t have to miss a single talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“I can watch the program\Nwith the rest of the brotherhood worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.66,0:00:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so thankful to Jehovah\Nfor this arrangement.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.91,0:01:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you can relate to her expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.29,0:01:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the generous donations\Nyou have made online
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.25,0:01:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at donate.jw.org and by other means,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.01,0:01:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which help make\Nthese streaming services possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.85,0:01:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,During these critical last days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.52,0:01:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,many families lack the affection
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.77,0:01:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah designed us to give and receive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.11,0:01:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, God’s Word contains principles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.53,0:01:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that, when followed, lead to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sure you will enjoy\Nthe fine talks and dramatizations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in this next symposium.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.91,0:01:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Joel Dellinger,\Na helper to the Service Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.67,0:01:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will deliver the first talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.96,0:01:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace\N—Show Love and Respect.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.23,0:02:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Family peace is precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s even as the Bible proverb says:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.73,0:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Better is a piece of dry bread\Nwhere there is peace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,than a house full of feasting\Nalong with quarreling.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But what exactly is family peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.08,0:02:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone might say, “As long as we’re not\Narguing, our family is at peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But is that real peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We might think of two countries\Nthat were fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but have now agreed to a cease-fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.09,0:02:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the cease-fire mean that they’ve become
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.55,0:02:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,real friends who love one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.26,0:02:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.80,0:02:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that genuine peace takes more work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true in the family as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our heavenly Father knows\Nthat the most satisfying family peace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,involves more than an absence of arguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.03,0:02:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It involves a family’s well-being and unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:03:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is such peace in a family today\Nreally possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.83,0:03:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Although none of us have a perfect family,\Nthe answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.17,0:03:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,While it requires work\N—perhaps breaking bad habits
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.75,0:03:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that disrupt peace and adopting\Nnew ones that promote it—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.22,0:03:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,those efforts are worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.68,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see how Bible principles\Ncan guide families to peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just as a road map
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.69,0:03:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,guides travelers to a beautiful destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.06,0:03:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In each of the talks,\Nwe invite you husbands, fathers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,wives, mothers, children, teenagers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the traveler who studies the map
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.16,0:03:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and then goes in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.29,0:03:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus of our first talk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.29,0:03:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is showing love and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.00,0:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you say these two qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are so important to family peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.47,0:03:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s simple:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.47,0:04:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because family members\Nwho love and respect one another
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.72,0:04:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,feel secure and appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.39,0:04:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, our relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.06,0:04:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are warm, close, and peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.98,0:04:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, showing love and respect\Ncan be a challenge these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.78,0:04:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization notice why.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.87,0:04:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you look so handsome there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.62,0:04:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you look beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.34,0:04:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Those came out so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.55,0:04:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Crazy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re so surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I just knew you were going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it’s OK, Sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.85,0:04:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.14,0:04:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I’m all moved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last box.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.61,0:04:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, are those the wedding photos?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.90,0:04:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.78,0:04:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Look it. Here’s . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.95,0:05:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you all look beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That dress looks so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.87,0:05:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww, look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.33,0:05:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww, that suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.37,0:05:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it all came together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It really did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.02,0:05:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this is all new, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.49,0:05:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I cut in?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.91,0:05:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.14,0:06:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.93,0:06:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Where’s the desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.44,0:06:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.77,0:06:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is better for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.82,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean it’s better for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.28,0:06:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For Max?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.28,0:06:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.49,0:06:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t talk to me like that. Get back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Olivia, what do you think\Nabout the desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.32,0:07:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, sweetie. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.54,0:07:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you never forget that I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, every family\Nfaces challenges of some sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.05,0:07:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s consult our road map together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible at Romans 12:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.89,0:07:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you read it with me, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.69,0:07:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Romans 12:10:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“In brotherly love
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.40,0:07:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“have tender affection for one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.07,0:07:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In showing honor to one another,\Ntake the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.66,0:07:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the role we play in the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.91,0:07:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,each of us needs to treat our family members\Nwith love and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.67,0:08:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to “take the lead,”\Nor initiative, to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.76,0:08:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us, let’s consider four good habits
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that all of us should work\Nto develop more fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Habit number one:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Regularly express tender affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When conveyed with sincerity,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.85,0:08:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions of affection
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.86,0:08:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are like sunshine and water to plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They help everyone\Nin the family grow and thrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video we just watched,\Ndid you note how Olivia
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.74,0:08:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,cherished her father’s gift (that green desk)\Nand his tender words?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.54,0:08:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He told her,\N“So you never forget that I love you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.38,0:08:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We also saw warm affection
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as the newly blended family\Nof Max and Irene looked at wedding photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.18,0:08:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That was encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here’s a question: How are we doing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.43,0:08:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in expressing tender affection in our family?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.10,0:08:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s not one of our strengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.44,0:08:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we might relate to a husband\Nwho mustered up the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.56,0:09:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to say “I love you” to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.03,0:09:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It brought her to tears—tears of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.07,0:09:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said this, “I love you too,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is the first time in 25 years\Nyou’ve said it like that.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.96,0:09:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t want to wait that long, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.54,0:09:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but even an awkward attempt\Nat expressing affection in our family
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.13,0:09:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act of love,\Nand it can do so much good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.63,0:09:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a habit we all want to cultivate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.85,0:09:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider a second habit:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.39,0:09:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind in your actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.85,0:09:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,tone of voice, and choice of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.02,0:09:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video, we recall Irene’s reassurance\Nto her daughter, Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She said: “I know this is all new, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.40,0:09:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.07,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom was kind
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.07,0:09:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in what she said and how she said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.37,0:09:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A little later, though, Olivia was upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.25,0:09:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,While we know she was hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.33,0:10:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,her speech and actions were not so kind,\Nwere they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.34,0:10:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,During the pandemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.30,0:10:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us have been under tremendous stress,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.34,0:10:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and likely we didn’t always treat others
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.18,0:10:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in our family as kindly\Nas we would have liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.18,0:10:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.06,0:10:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But what can we all do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.89,0:10:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We can pray to Jehovah\Nto help us “take the lead”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.40,0:10:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in showing kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.69,0:10:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nevery day greeting one another kindly,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.36,0:10:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,every day saying “please” and “thank you,”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.11,0:10:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing little gifts,\Nmaking time to talk, really listening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of these are acts of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.75,0:10:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a good habit we all want to cultivate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s habit number three?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.00,0:10:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quick to apologize and forgive freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.80,0:10:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video, Olivia’s new stepsister, Sue,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.01,0:10:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,apologized after she bumped into Olivia\Nwith a box by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.39,0:10:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That apology promoted peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When you and I realize we’ve hurt someone
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.98,0:11:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,even unintentionally, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We should make amends quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A mother named Marina said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.16,0:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“We try to set a good example\Nfor our children
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.99,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“in forgiving others\N. . . and not getting offended.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I am wrong, I apologize to my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.62,0:11:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to learn to do the same\Nin their dealings with others.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.63,0:11:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a good habit, wouldn’t you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider one more,\Na fourth habit:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Help your family members feel respected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,An article in the {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Awake!{\r}  magazine\Nonce made this insightful comment:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.81,0:11:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Respect is in the eye of the beholder.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.36,0:11:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we think\Nwe’re showing respect in the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.49,0:11:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,good questions to ask ourselves are:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.82,0:11:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do my family members\Nfeel that I respect them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:12:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Is there more I can do to help my mate,\Nmy children, or my parents
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.16,0:12:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,feel loved and respected?’
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.34,0:12:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters, when we fulfill\Nour God-given role in the family
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.13,0:12:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by developing good habits such as these,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.93,0:12:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we show respect both for Jehovah\Nand for all of our family members.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.89,0:12:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s think about Olivia and her mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.56,0:12:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next video,\Nnote how peace can be restored
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.90,0:12:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,by showing love and respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.45,0:12:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s OK, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.75,0:12:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.91,0:12:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad did that for her just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.46,0:12:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything I can do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:12:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 12:10:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.89,0:13:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor to one another,\Ntake the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.19,0:13:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.41,0:13:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I made your favorite tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to tell you\Nthat I didn’t handle that so well today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.76,0:13:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You had good reason\Nto be upset about the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.52,0:13:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you didn’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.69,0:13:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just one of those things\Nthat Dad did just for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.74,0:13:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I know he’s my stepdad now, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.91,0:14:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wish he would have checked first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.45,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t Max.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.96,0:14:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to surprise Max\Nwith a place for him to do his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.42,0:14:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn’t make you get rid of the desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.34,0:14:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.35,0:14:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought you both didn’t care.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.02,0:14:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never ever stop caring about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.29,0:14:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful outcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The well-being and unity\Nof the family were restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.30,0:14:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The mom, Irene,\Napplied the principle at Romans 12:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.47,0:15:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She ‘took the lead,’ or the initiative,\Nto talk kindly with her daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.39,0:15:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Though Olivia was upset,\Nshe too showed love and respect
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.35,0:15:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by being willing to listen to her mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.81,0:15:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,\Nthe misunderstanding was cleared up,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and Irene used the opportunity to reassure\Nher precious daughter of her love,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.03,0:15:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, “I will never ever\Nstop caring about you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.99,0:15:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And how our hearts were touched
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to see their warm embrace!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When we “take the lead”\Nin applying Bible principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.67,0:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we promote genuine family peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So may all of us be determined
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.80,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep showing our family\Nthat we truly love and respect them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in word and action.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.77,0:15:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now please listen as Brother Robert Luccioni,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.64,0:15:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Publishing Committee,\Nconsiders the next talk
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.02,0:15:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of this symposium, with the theme 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.65,0:15:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace\N—Improve Communication.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our previous talk reminded us
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s possible\Nfor a family to enjoy peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it takes work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.34,0:16:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at one more step\Nthat can help us stay on the road to peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.05,0:16:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is good communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A family promotes peace\Nwhen all the family members communicate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in an open, calm, and honest manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But how does communication help with peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.65,0:16:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a pattern of good communication\Nkeeps a family close.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.24,0:16:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps us to identify and address problems
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.28,0:16:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,before these reach a point\Nthat they take peace away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.03,0:16:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that may seem obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.25,0:16:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn’t it true that we may find\Nthat between work and school,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.50,0:16:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the meetings and ministry,\Nand recreation and just life in general
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:17:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s hard to find time\Nto communicate as a family?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.01,0:17:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a challenge in your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.68,0:17:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,notice what habits\Nhinder family communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.07,0:17:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I’m sorry I was late to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.08,0:17:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have been there\Nto help out with my assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.58,0:17:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we got delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.50,0:17:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re late!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.80,0:17:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go, kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.51,0:17:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re coming! Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the family is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.47,0:17:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is adjusting really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.48,0:17:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone seen my glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.95,0:18:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we might be a little out of sync,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.95,0:18:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don’t know
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.29,0:18:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—every family has their issues, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.13,0:18:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You going outside in those?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.76,0:18:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, well, thanks for understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.56,0:18:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.88,0:19:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice some habits\Nthat hinder family communication?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.97,0:19:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the case of this family, it seems like
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,technology is stifling their communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.39,0:19:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And they obviously have some things\Nthey need to communicate about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.94,0:19:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—punctuality, dress and grooming—\Nbut it’s not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.32,0:19:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, while the scenes of them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all looking at their devices\Nand ignoring one another
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,may have been a bit humorous,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.99,0:19:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,did it remind you of your family at times?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What a good reminder\Nfor us not to let the use of technology
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.04,0:19:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,rob our family of our time and attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.13,0:19:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we develop habits
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.26,0:19:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that promote good communication?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.88,0:19:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider the second Bible principle\Nof this symposium.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn together, please,\Nto Ephesians chapter 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.43,0:19:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s read verses 15 and 16
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:19:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—Ephesians 5:15, 16:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.61,0:20:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“So keep strict watch that how you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.02,0:20:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“walk is not as unwise but as wise persons,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.11,0:20:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“making the best use of your time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.91,0:20:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because the days are wicked.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.20,0:20:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s look at two ways\Nthat this Bible principle can help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.29,0:20:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is by making time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to have meaningful communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.75,0:20:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice there in verse 16
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.25,0:20:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it says “making the best use of your time”?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.09,0:20:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the study note for this phrase indicates
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.34,0:20:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the need to ‘buy out the time’\Nfor important things
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from other pursuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.85,0:20:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can this apply\Nto family communication?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.27,0:20:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this could include\Nhaving a plan, or a routine,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.44,0:20:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for when we spend time together\Nas a family each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.61,0:20:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And during those times,\Nwe may choose to limit
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.20,0:20:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our use of technology so that it\Ndoes not interfere with communication;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.74,0:20:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps it’s in the evening\Nor at a specific mealtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.42,0:21:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One brother named Aaron stated,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.67,0:21:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have our evening meal together,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.05,0:21:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“which allows us time to talk\Nand hear what’s important
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.01,0:21:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to each member of the family.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.09,0:21:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “My wife and I\Nhave arranged our schedules
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.05,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“so we take the boys\Nto school and pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This allows us to spend more time with them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.60,0:21:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he says,\N“My wife and I regularly take walks
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and freely talk about our concerns.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.86,0:21:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they’re making good use of their time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.74,0:21:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,However, to do this, they’ve had to buy\Nthat time out from other pursuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.99,0:21:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But they have a plan; they have a routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.16,0:21:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what plan, or routine,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.83,0:21:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,does your family have\Nfor meaningful communication each day?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.17,0:21:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t have one, can you start now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.80,0:21:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at the second way\Nthat this Bible principle can help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.14,0:21:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is by determining when and how
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.68,0:22:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to deal with problems when they do arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.77,0:22:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice verse 15 in Ephesians chapter 5
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,says that we should ‘walk as wise persons.’
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.15,0:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It means we need\Nto choose our paths carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.11,0:22:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing when to go, when to stop,\Nwhen to take another route.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.12,0:22:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can that help us\Nwhen problems arise?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.75,0:22:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a wise person
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,generally knows when is and when is not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.59,0:22:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a good time to address a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.96,0:22:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, we all can attest\Nthat when emotions are high,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.63,0:22:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s probably not the best time\Nto bring up an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.93,0:22:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One father states:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.14,0:22:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sometimes we need to wait\Nand let things cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.35,0:22:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Often a night’s rest\Nwith prayer makes a big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.65,0:22:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when we address the issue the next morning.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.11,0:22:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a wise person.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.44,0:22:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A wise person also listens.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.91,0:22:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,James 1:19 reminds us to “be quick to listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.95,0:23:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,slow to speak, [and] slow to anger.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.08,0:23:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, we can go to Jehovah in prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.12,0:23:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask him to help us to really listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.09,0:23:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay calm, to stay humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.51,0:23:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One sister named Dawn states,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.84,0:23:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“When there are problems,\Nthe first thing I do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.80,0:23:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is ask Jehovah in prayer to help us\Nresolve the problem calmly.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.31,0:23:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she says, “Then we talk\Nwith the family member privately
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.27,0:23:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and really try to listen\Nto their side of the issue.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.73,0:23:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a wise person.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.03,0:23:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A wise person will also consider the approach
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.20,0:23:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the words that he or she uses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.66,0:23:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, rather than telling\Nour family member that they have a problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.12,0:23:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can we turn it around so that it’s something\Nthat we all need to work on together?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.58,0:23:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you reassure your family members
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.38,0:23:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that you really love them\Nand you want to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.17,0:23:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,their side of the issue or the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.93,0:23:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See, now, doing this,\Nwe’re not attacking the family member
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.56,0:24:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather,\Nshowing that we’re all in this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.10,0:24:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see benefits of this Bible principle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.56,0:24:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in communication in our family, don’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.32,0:24:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice the two points:\N(1) making the best use of our time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.86,0:24:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and (2) walking as wise persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.70,0:24:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, communication will always be\Na work in progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.29,0:24:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s worth the effort,\Nas it will go a long way
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.46,0:24:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to bringing peace to your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.04,0:24:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch more of our dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.75,0:24:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice the benefits of developing habits
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.88,0:24:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that promote good communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.31,0:24:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.39,0:24:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.10,0:24:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have to work on it.\NI know I need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.86,0:24:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t we approach it that way\Nwith the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.11,0:24:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—just be open with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.19,0:24:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds like a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.57,0:25:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. So Irene and I have been talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.16,0:25:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,communication
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.16,0:25:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.79,0:25:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to talk\Nabout our phones and other devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.50,0:25:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not talking about me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.04,0:25:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.67,0:25:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.09,0:25:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that we can all be\Nmore balanced, but . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.50,0:25:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.51,0:25:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re joking, right? You mean them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.05,0:25:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t take them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.84,0:25:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t done anything bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.97,0:25:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.09,0:25:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.64,0:25:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re always on your phone too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.68,0:25:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.39,0:25:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.76,0:25:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just talk about it, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.35,0:25:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sue,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.56,0:25:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can you read Ephesians 5:15, 16\Nfor us, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.90,0:25:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“So keep strict watch that how you walk
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.41,0:25:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“is not as unwise but as wise persons,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.62,0:25:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,making the best use of your time,\Nbecause the days are wicked.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.71,0:25:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.50,0:25:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you think we’re doing\Nwith our phones and other devices?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.47,0:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn’t that what you’re doing\Non your devices is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.93,0:26:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.73,0:26:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But could it be taking time away\Nfrom more important things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.23,0:26:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—like talking to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.03,0:26:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and in that way affecting even\Nhow we’re talking to each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.74,0:26:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think it’d be smart
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.79,0:26:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to have some boundaries then.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.71,0:26:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.88,0:26:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.35,0:26:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.72,0:26:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s talk about how we can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.77,0:26:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.98,0:26:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.23,0:26:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.36,0:26:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, I haven’t figured out\Nhow to talk to her about her clothes yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.82,0:27:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.36,0:27:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.11,0:27:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.83,0:27:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.96,0:27:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s all about good spiritual judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.08,0:27:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that these trends reflect\NJehovah’s view of “respectable dress”?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.47,0:27:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you’ll do the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.80,0:27:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.31,0:27:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Gabe, can you take us?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.68,0:27:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.73,0:27:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.98,0:27:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,While we’re all here,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.60,0:27:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know we all have\Ndifferent views on punctuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.90,0:27:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.07,0:27:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I really need your help
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.78,0:27:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can take care\Nof some of my responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.91,0:27:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You think we can meet in the middle?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.29,0:27:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.79,0:27:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.29,0:27:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.77,0:28:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this symposium has been discussing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.40,0:28:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,four Bible principles\Nthat can guide families to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.32,0:28:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dellinger considered the first one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.03,0:28:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 12:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.36,0:28:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this part, we considered\NEphesians chapter 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.37,0:28:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 15, 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.58,0:28:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, did we see how this scripture\Nhelped our family in the video?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.92,0:28:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we saw that they knew down deep\Nthat they were not making
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.38,0:28:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the best use of their time,\Nso they made changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.96,0:28:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They saw that they needed to set boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.13,0:28:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could improve\Ntheir communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.89,0:28:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We also saw how the family\N—the parents—acted as wise persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.93,0:28:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.98,0:28:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by determining when and how
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to address the problems\Nthat needed to be addressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the use of technology,\Ndress and grooming,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.53,0:29:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and punctuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.86,0:29:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, can this Bible principle\Nhelp your family
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.03,0:29:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—help my family—to improve communication?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.33,0:29:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Would this be a good scripture to include
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.87,0:29:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in your next family worship?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.92,0:29:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it takes time to learn how\Nto communicate well as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.59,0:29:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is worth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.05,0:29:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.47,0:29:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we strive to communicate\Nwell each day,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.14,0:29:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then communication will come more readily
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.64,0:29:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when there are problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.64,0:29:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So be determined to look for ways
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.60,0:29:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve communication in your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.77,0:29:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And by taking this initiative\Nand sticking with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.98,0:29:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be following the road map
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.57,0:29:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to family peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.28,0:29:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please listen now to Brother David Splane,\Na member of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.62,0:29:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as he considers the next talk\Nof this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.04,0:30:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace\N—Work as a Team.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.64,0:30:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah intended married couples\Nto work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.43,0:30:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why Jesus used the expression we find
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.18,0:30:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 19:6.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.10,0:30:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read this from the Bible\N—Matthew 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.03,0:30:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll give you a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.11,0:30:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 19\N—now, we’re going to read verse 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.53,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, first of all, Jesus quotes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.08,0:30:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from Genesis 2:24.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.83,0:30:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of married couples, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.42,0:30:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“So that they are no longer two,\Nbut one flesh.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.30,0:30:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you remember, Jehovah\Nmade that comment in the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.05,0:30:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But now Jesus adds something\Nthat isn’t in Genesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.26,0:30:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “Therefore, what God has yoked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.23,0:31:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“[yoked] together,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.02,0:31:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,let no man put apart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.61,0:31:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think of a yoke,\Nwe may think of a team of horses
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.61,0:31:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,plowing a field or pulling a heavy wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.70,0:31:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if they pull together,\Nthey can be a powerful force.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.79,0:31:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is true\Nwhen family members work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.25,0:31:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, Dad
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.05,0:31:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—you have excellent reasons to work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.92,0:31:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you work together,\Nyou contribute to the peace of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.72,0:31:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And think of the effect\Nit has on the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.18,0:31:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By working together, you’re teaching\Nthat fine young son of yours
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.19,0:31:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how to be a caring husband and father,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.44,0:31:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and your beautiful daughter how to be\Na supportive wife and mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.36,0:31:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happens when teammates\Nbegin pulling in opposite directions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.28,0:31:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or when one puts on the brakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.74,0:31:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch a video.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.79,0:31:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s the setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.83,0:32:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For a long time, a sister raised\Nher two children as a single parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.00,0:32:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and she did a great job of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.38,0:32:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she married a very kind brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.22,0:32:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The family has a new head.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.22,0:32:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see how well the sister\Nis adapting to her new role.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.27,0:32:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The last few weeks of family worship\Nhave been nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.52,0:32:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.27,0:32:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.86,0:32:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things we ask and pray\Nin Jesus’ name, Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.65,0:32:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.62,0:32:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, this week . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.58,0:32:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in chapter 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.08,0:32:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, that’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.66,0:32:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And last week, Gabe read, so this week . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.92,0:32:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Sue’s turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.09,0:32:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.\NIt’s Sue’s turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.92,0:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, the point here is\Nthat when it comes . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.92,0:32:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, maybe an illustration would be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.60,0:32:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.77,0:33:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a bird . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.06,0:33:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, hopefully I was able to clear that up\Nfor you a little bit, Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.23,0:33:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.02,0:33:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, actually, Max, that’s not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.69,0:33:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We had an updated understanding\Nin the recent {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Watchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.86,0:33:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.45,0:33:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they went really well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.33,0:33:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, actually . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.21,0:33:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.80,0:33:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we can talk about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.35,0:33:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.86,0:33:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The sister isn’t a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.41,0:33:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can ask:\NWhat is she teaching her daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.28,0:34:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,about the wife’s role in the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.54,0:34:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is her son learning\Nabout taking the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.04,0:34:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as the man of the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.08,0:34:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn’t had a man\Nin his life for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.38,0:34:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.42,0:34:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s safe to say that the kids\Nwill stand a better chance
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.34,0:34:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of having a successful marriage themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.80,0:34:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when they see their parents pulling together.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.39,0:34:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A little later, we’ll see how\Nthe husband handles the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.52,0:34:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we brothers\Nare going to want to pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.27,0:34:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a classic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Family life is more pleasant when Dad, Mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.99,0:34:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kids work together as a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.03,0:34:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The family head is the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.20,0:34:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs to make sure that everyone knows
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.33,0:34:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what goals the family is working toward
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.66,0:34:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and how each one can contribute\Ntoward achieving those goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.25,0:34:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When it’s your family’s turn\Nto help clean the Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.30,0:34:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or a convention venue, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.92,0:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t leave the kids at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.97,0:34:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re part of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.59,0:35:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t go there with half the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.85,0:35:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them experience the joy\Nthat comes from serving others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.10,0:35:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them work along with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.52,0:35:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re assigned to clean the restrooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.73,0:35:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t complain about it—a very fine example.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.82,0:35:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your children will learn that when\Nthere’s work to be done, we just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.20,0:35:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We aren’t picky about what we will\Nand will not do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.12,0:35:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don’t feel\Nthat some jobs are beneath us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.66,0:35:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is in line with Paul’s counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.00,0:35:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,found at Philippians 2:3, 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.25,0:35:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.47,0:35:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.76,0:35:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—Philippians chapter 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.47,0:35:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 3, 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.85,0:35:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’re thinking about the family\Nas a team here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.10,0:35:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Do nothing out of contentiousness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.07,0:35:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“or out of egotism,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“but with humility consider\Nothers superior to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.41,0:36:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“as you look out\Nnot only for your own interests,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.24,0:36:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but also for the interests of others.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.21,0:36:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When there’s work to be done,\Nsomeone has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.42,0:36:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I think that I’m so special\Nthat someone else has to look after it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.51,0:36:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Some families volunteer\Nto help with Kingdom Hall maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.97,0:36:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When the kids are old enough,\Nthey can work on other projects
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.64,0:36:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like working on an Assembly Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.60,0:36:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.35,0:36:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The friendships that you\Nand your young people will forge
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.52,0:36:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,can last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.65,0:36:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s a bonus: When the young people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.98,0:36:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,go to a circuit assembly\Nor a regional convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.78,0:36:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they’ll have good friends to associate with
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.53,0:36:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—both young and old—\Npeople they’ve been working with.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.16,0:36:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What about working around the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.37,0:36:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Some parents feel that the children\Nshouldn’t have to help out at all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.13,0:36:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have their schoolwork to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.05,0:36:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But their schoolwork is something\Nthey do for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.92,0:37:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they contributing\Nto the welfare of the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.43,0:37:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they learning\Nto serve others unselfishly?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.31,0:37:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good for a child to feel that he has\Nan important role in the household
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.06,0:37:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and that people are counting on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.31,0:37:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Think what that does for his self-respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.07,0:37:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A father named Steven said,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.61,0:37:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“When nothing is expected of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.07,0:37:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“children learn that they\Nare here to be served,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.83,0:37:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they grow up with a distorted view
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.49,0:37:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of what life will require of them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.67,0:37:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We might ask, Would a young person
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.13,0:37:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with that attitude\Neven be able to keep a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.21,0:37:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When some in the world lose their job,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.63,0:37:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they remain unemployed for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.47,0:37:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They can’t pay the bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.26,0:37:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, there are job opportunities\Nall around them,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.85,0:37:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but they consider those jobs beneath them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.19,0:37:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And what’s one of the most annoying traits\Nan employee can have?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.57,0:37:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask any boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.57,0:38:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When the worker is asked to do something,\Nhe replies,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.57,0:38:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“That’s not my job.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.49,0:38:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Teach your child that anything\Nthat needs to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.24,0:38:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is his job if he’s old enough\Nand capable of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.29,0:38:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How early should parents\Nstart to assign chores to their children?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.50,0:38:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Some experts have found that children who are
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.92,0:38:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,three years old or even younger
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.80,0:38:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,can be taught to help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.39,0:38:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They can learn to pick up their toys,\Nclean up spills, sort laundry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.02,0:38:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Older children can vacuum,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.31,0:38:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wash the car, prepare a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.11,0:38:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m happy to say that many young brothers\Nhere at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.11,0:38:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are excellent cooks,\Nwhich is often the result
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.95,0:38:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of fine parental training.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.03,0:38:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the video where Caleb
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.41,0:38:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is taught to clean his room\Nand put away his toys?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.21,0:38:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That video was a game changer\Nfor many children.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.83,0:38:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to be just like Caleb.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.71,0:39:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And now when you enter their room,\Nyou can find the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.97,0:39:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When problems arise,\Nattack the problem, not each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.76,0:39:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not ‘How can I win?’\Nbut ‘How can we win?’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.02,0:39:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see an excellent example of that\Nin the follow-up video.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.40,0:39:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.49,0:39:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.00,0:39:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Want some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.62,0:39:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.96,0:39:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, babe,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.34,0:39:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you and me, we’re a team, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.14,0:39:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.26,0:39:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When I read this, I thought about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.73,0:40:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“So that they are no longer two,\Nbut one flesh.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.24,0:40:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that before, you had to shoulder\Neverything yourself for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.99,0:40:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.74,0:40:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you did great.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.24,0:40:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been raising two beautiful,\Nspiritual kids on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.96,0:40:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But now you have me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.83,0:40:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.34,0:40:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So do you think\Nsometimes we’re not a team?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.67,0:40:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s just that sometimes\Nduring family worship . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.93,0:40:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I get excited, and I jump in. I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.80,0:40:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m just so used to doing it\Nafter all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.89,0:40:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you’re not trying to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.10,0:40:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And listen, I love the way you teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.60,0:40:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see how you can reach the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.61,0:40:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways that I can’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.57,0:40:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me guide it,\Nand I’ll make sure you can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.24,0:40:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, honey. Thanks for your patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.37,0:40:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you for your patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.70,0:40:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a work in progress,\Nbut we make a great team.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.63,0:41:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t we look at what we’re going\Nto cover before our next family worship?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.63,0:41:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds great.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.68,0:41:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn’t that a fine example
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.85,0:41:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of how to attack a problem and not your mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.10,0:41:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No arguments, no raised voices,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.69,0:41:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,no accusations\N—the husband had empathy for his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.53,0:41:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t question her motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.53,0:41:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He realized that as a single parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.49,0:41:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,she’d been taking the lead for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.95,0:41:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice how she responded\Nto her husband’s kind counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.29,0:41:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt it’s going to be easy\Nfor the kids to respect their stepfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.92,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re going to learn\Nhow a husband and wife
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.00,0:41:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,should treat each other\Nand how they should pull together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.01,0:41:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime soon, you might want\Nto consider these questions:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.43,0:41:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In what aspects of our marriage\Ndo we work well as a team?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.06,0:42:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, how can we improve?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.10,0:42:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It pleases Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.32,0:42:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,when family members work together as a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.40,0:42:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That promotes peace in the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.90,0:42:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And our God is a “God of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.74,0:42:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Brother John Ekrann
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.54,0:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,will consider the final talk\Nof this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.42,0:42:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Follow the Road Map to Family Peace
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.67,0:42:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—Worship Jehovah Together.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.76,0:42:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants your family\Nto be happy and peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.43,0:42:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah does more than simply say,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.44,0:42:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“I hope you have a peaceful family life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.06,0:42:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He explains exactly how we\Ncan get our family there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.40,0:42:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to imagine Jehovah\Nlaying out a map in front of you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.57,0:42:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying: “See these landmarks?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.82,0:42:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look for them on the road to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.28,0:42:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you see them,\Nyou’re going in the right direction.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.46,0:43:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So far in this symposium, we’ve passed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.62,0:43:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the landmarks of showing love and respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.46,0:43:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,improving communication,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.46,0:43:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and working together as a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.80,0:43:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The last landmark\Nwe’ll consider in this symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.18,0:43:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is worshipping together as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.18,0:43:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Worshipping together as a family
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.31,0:43:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,promotes peace and brings his blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.31,0:43:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if not all in your family\Nare worshippers of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.27,0:43:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can promote peace\Nby maintaining a very good spiritual routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.65,0:43:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,\Nnotice some common obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.32,0:43:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to worshipping Jehovah as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.58,0:43:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.21,0:43:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, babe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.96,0:43:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s for family worship this week?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.01,0:43:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I got some good ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.39,0:43:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.80,0:43:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.97,0:44:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for reading that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.47,0:44:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Um.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.06,0:44:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just go ahead and ask the question.\NWe’ll just do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.77,0:44:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So paragraphs 13 and 14:\N“How can we be generous?”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.44,0:44:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.95,0:44:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the footnote that we just read\Nreally helps us to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.29,0:44:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the definition of that quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.21,0:44:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the definition, we’re left to wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.13,0:44:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what it is\Nand how it connects to the other things
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.13,0:44:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ve discussed this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.51,0:44:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabe, can you go ahead\Nand read the next one for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.01,0:44:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.43,0:44:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.51,0:44:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible contains many examples\Nof submissive individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.15,0:44:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So are there examples?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.44,0:44:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.36,0:44:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.07,0:44:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.15,0:44:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about examples,\Nwhere do we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.07,0:44:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There are examples in the past;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.74,0:45:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,there are even examples presently.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.45,0:45:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we could even be examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.67,0:45:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s—that’s the power of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.55,0:45:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.77,0:45:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a lot of reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.60,0:45:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to enjoy family worship, but
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.15,0:45:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like the things that we are covering
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.24,0:45:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,are just really not what I need right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.61,0:45:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.45,0:45:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I just don’t know\Nif this is what they need right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.66,0:45:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.00,0:45:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll keep working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.84,0:46:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we’d all agree that family worship\Nwas difficult to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.39,0:46:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was uncomfortable for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.93,0:46:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly, Max and Irene had some obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.60,0:46:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they needed to overcome\Nto really worshipping Jehovah as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.61,0:46:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To start and keep a good habit going
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.82,0:46:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,requires determination and resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.57,0:46:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s where you need\Nto start for your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.07,0:46:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to resolve
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.07,0:46:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re going\Nto worship Jehovah as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.12,0:46:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the resolve in Joshua’s words
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.62,0:46:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at Joshua 24:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.33,0:46:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Joshua 24:15:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.34,0:46:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now if it seems bad to you to serve Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.47,0:46:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“choose for yourselves today\Nwhom you will serve,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.64,0:46:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“whether the gods that your forefathers\Nserved on the other side of the River
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.06,0:46:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“or the gods of the Amorites\Nin whose land you are dwelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.06,0:46:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as for me and my household,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.11,0:46:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we will serve Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.53,0:47:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, worship of Jehovah as a family
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.16,0:47:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to be at the very center\Nof your family life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.49,0:47:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, weekly family worship
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.50,0:47:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is not all that’s involved\Nin worshipping together as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.66,0:47:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider five ways
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.83,0:47:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we can worship Jehovah together as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.80,0:47:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,(1) Prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.42,0:47:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents, do not underestimate the impact
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.93,0:47:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that your prayers have on your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.89,0:47:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When a child hears their parents\Npour out their hearts to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.64,0:47:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that tells them that Jehovah\Nis very real to their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.90,0:47:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can recall growing up listening\Nto my father’s prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.98,0:47:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when I was young,\NI thought his prayers were very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.99,0:47:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I grew older and really\Nlistened carefully to what he was saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.83,0:47:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see how much of a close relationship\Nhe had with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.12,0:47:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,(2) Discuss the daily text.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.04,0:47:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s an excellent habit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.05,0:47:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and a very spiritual way to start the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.80,0:48:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(3) Attend meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.14,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’re not just making sure our family\Nis there at the meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.47,0:48:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but that they’re involved and engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.18,0:48:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And work hard to prepare\Nso that all family members
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.89,0:48:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can have a meaningful comment\Nat the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.77,0:48:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,(4) Share in the ministry regularly\Nas a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.24,0:48:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sharing in the ministry together\Nas a family
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.86,0:48:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,draws us closer to our family members.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.45,0:48:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When we hear them speak about the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.20,0:48:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we listen to their phone calls,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.33,0:48:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or we read their letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.67,0:48:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we can feel their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.33,0:48:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved going in the ministry with my mother
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.96,0:48:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and listening to her skillfully use the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.05,0:48:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to answer questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.01,0:48:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And (5) have a consistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.97,0:48:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyable,\Nand meaningful Family Worship program.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.35,0:48:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider what that means\N—first of all, consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.06,0:48:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video, Max was trying to have
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.48,0:49:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the family worship consistently each week.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.32,0:49:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your family worship consistent each week?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.66,0:49:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your family worship enjoyable?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.20,0:49:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the video, the kids were bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.87,0:49:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking at their phones\Nand checking the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.66,0:49:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And week after week\Nof kind of a question-and-answer style
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.34,0:49:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,led to the young people\Ngiving sort of one-word answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.84,0:49:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It did not look enjoyable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.26,0:49:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, would your family\Ndescribe family worship as enjoyable?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.85,0:49:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How about meaningful?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.56,0:49:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What Max was using for material
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.56,0:49:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was material that he thought was meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.11,0:49:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But did it look like it \Nwas meaningful to the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.40,0:49:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Does your family worship use material\Nthat is meaningful to your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.32,0:49:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after reviewing these five points,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.99,0:49:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t want you to be discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.33,0:49:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if it’s a struggle\Nto maintain a good routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.50,0:49:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Life in this system has many challenges,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.79,0:50:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,trials, and unexpected events.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.63,0:50:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So stay positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.84,0:50:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And when your good routine\Nbreaks down from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.97,0:50:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,consider what adjustments you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.26,0:50:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to be successful and get\Nyour spiritual routine back on track.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.23,0:50:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Regularly ask Jehovah for his help,\Nand don’t give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.19,0:50:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you watch\Nthe following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.61,0:50:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how Max and Irene\Nand the family worked together
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.15,0:50:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to make family worship successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.79,0:50:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,March 15, 2014, {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Watchtower, 
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.33,0:50:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Family Worship\N—Can you Make It More Enjoyable?”:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.67,0:50:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“The worship of Jehovah\Nshould not be boring. . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.88,0:50:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Address the needs of each family member.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.51,0:50:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Babe, what do our kids need?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.44,0:50:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s actually going on in their lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.35,0:51:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Family worship needs to include that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.48,0:51:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, maybe we need to pay more attention\Nto what’s going on with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.78,0:51:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to them; listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.29,0:51:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to send you a link\Nto a great {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Watchtower{\r}  article.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.21,0:51:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t wait to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.21,0:51:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Max and I changed our approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.76,0:51:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We found out what mattered to our kids
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.72,0:51:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—like friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.47,0:51:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . adjusting to a blended family,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.35,0:51:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . dating.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.78,0:51:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we turned things around\Nand used family worship
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.12,0:51:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to focus on what our kids really needed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.72,0:52:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and to prepare ourselves\Nfor possible future trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.40,0:52:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, y’all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.36,0:52:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.57,0:52:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.95,0:52:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.91,0:52:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.45,0:52:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,family worship was—was cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.95,0:52:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.08,0:52:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m glad you liked it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.33,0:52:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.62,0:52:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, y’all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.67,0:52:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.46,0:52:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.21,0:52:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Guess what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.71,0:52:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.05,0:52:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.84,0:52:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I applied to Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.97,0:52:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.97,0:52:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.80,0:52:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s really exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.06,0:52:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.14,0:53:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.56,0:53:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww, congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.61,0:53:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.98,0:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it’s selfie time, everybody.\NCome on, let’s get together.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.86,0:53:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. On three\Nwe’re going to say Bethel, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.66,0:53:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.20,0:53:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.79,0:53:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.10,0:53:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve come a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.49,0:53:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And through it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.28,0:53:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has taught us to love
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.58,0:54:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s given our family
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.08,0:54:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.82,0:55:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see that Max and Irene analyzed\Nwhat was wrong with family worship
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.53,0:55:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to change their approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.58,0:55:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s examine how they did that\Nand what it means for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.92,0:55:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they do to make their
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.59,0:55:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,family worship more meaningful?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.30,0:55:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Max and Irene had to ask themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.17,0:55:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what was going on in their kids’ lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.01,0:55:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What topics could they\Ndiscuss at family worship
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.10,0:55:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that would truly be useful to their kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.06,0:55:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you smile when you saw Max\Nalmost drop the glass
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.65,0:55:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when his daughter talked about dating?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.61,0:55:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But what a difference their efforts to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.69,0:55:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and really understand what was happening
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.95,0:55:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with the kids made in the family worship!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.28,0:56:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Max and Irene\Nmake family worship more enjoyable?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.91,0:56:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see how the family\Nwas reacting at family worship now?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.08,0:56:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What a difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.08,0:56:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids were smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.13,0:56:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked engaged in the discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.34,0:56:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and touched by what they were discussing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.63,0:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So do what you can\Nto make sure that your family
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.85,0:56:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,feels relaxed and happy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.14,0:56:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that your family worship reflects
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.52,0:56:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of happy\Nand joyful God that Jehovah is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.77,0:56:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, your family will often remember
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.65,0:56:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,more about how they felt\Nduring family worship
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.82,0:56:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,than maybe the exact details\Nof what they learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.95,0:56:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep worshipping Jehovah as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.37,0:56:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Make your family worship consistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.74,0:56:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyable, and meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.33,0:56:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And work together to overcome obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.42,0:56:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,just like Max and Irene and the kids\Nall worked together to solve problems
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.38,0:56:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and create a very peaceful family life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.43,0:57:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really beautiful to see how far
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.97,0:57:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they had come by applying Bible principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.85,0:57:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In review, this symposium has taught us
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.06,0:57:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that Bible principles can be used
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.31,0:57:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as a road map to family peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.48,0:57:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Work hard to show love and respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.40,0:57:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve communication,\Nto work together as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.28,0:57:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and to worship Jehovah together.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.58,0:57:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And please be patient with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.25,0:57:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as you form habits that lead to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.54,0:57:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, you and your family
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.88,0:57:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will enjoy peace that only he can provide.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.80,0:57:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.26,0:57:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We benefited from thinking\Nabout how we can apply
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.26,0:57:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible principles you shared
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.43,0:57:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the practical lessons\Nin the dramatizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.19,0:57:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us long to see true peace on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.48,0:57:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How will that be accomplished?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.78,0:58:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we prove\Nthat we honor and support
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.57,0:58:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s appointed King, Christ Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.45,0:58:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s listen as Brother Mark Noumair,\Na helper to the Teaching Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.21,0:58:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,provides these answers and more in the talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.96,0:58:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Loyally Support the ‘Prince of Peace.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.18,0:58:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the scene: It’s nighttime.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.14,0:58:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re in the garden of Gethsemane\Nwith your close friends and beloved Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.06,0:58:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, you hear a crowd coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.27,0:58:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re being led by a man you know,\NJudas Iscariot.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.07,0:58:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He approaches Jesus\Nand kisses him on the cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.78,0:58:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He then steps aside\Nas men move in to arrest Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.75,0:58:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your emotions churn inside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.08,0:58:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Master and Lord is being arrested\N—the Son of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.92,0:58:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How can this be happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.75,0:58:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.26,0:59:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you can even decide what to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.63,0:59:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter draws his sword
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.64,0:59:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and chops off the ear\Nof the slave of the high priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.64,0:59:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Jesus says to Peter:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.43,0:59:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Return your sword to its place,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.86,0:59:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for all those who take up the sword\Nwill perish by the sword.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.53,0:59:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you watch the unbelievable,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.74,0:59:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus heals the man’s ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.53,0:59:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter must have thought\Nthat it was a great and noble thing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.37,0:59:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to fight on behalf of the Son of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.54,0:59:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus didn’t think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.92,0:59:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,With six words
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.05,0:59:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—“return your sword to its place”—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.42,0:59:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus taught his disciples\Nan important lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.93,0:59:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This was not their fight;
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.27,0:59:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nor was it the time to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.98,0:59:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.40,1:00:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to focus our attention\Non an insidious way
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.61,1:00:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that any of us, like Peter,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.61,1:00:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,can become inadvertently involved\Nin this world’s conflicts
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.53,1:00:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,without even realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.87,1:00:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will talk about how we\Ncan avoid making that serious mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.54,1:00:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But first,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.54,1:00:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s discuss why Jesus\Ndid not ask his Father
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.46,1:00:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to send “12 legions of angels”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.26,1:00:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to help him when being arrested.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.72,1:00:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with Jesus’ name.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.72,1:00:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So please open your Bible\Nto Isaiah chapter 9,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.39,1:00:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read verse 6
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.65,1:00:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—Isaiah 9:6.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.19,1:00:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know Jesus has many titles,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.11,1:00:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but in this verse,\Nwe’re going to focus on just one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.45,1:00:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 6:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.79,1:00:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“For a child has been born to us,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.87,1:00:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“a son has been given to us;
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.42,1:01:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the rulership will rest on his shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.55,1:01:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“His name will be called Wonderful Counselor,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.17,1:01:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mighty God, Eternal Father,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.30,1:01:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Peace.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.85,1:01:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is Jesus called “Prince of Peace”?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.06,1:01:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, consider what Jehovah’s angel\N declared to the shepherds in the field
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.98,1:01:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,at Jesus’ birth at Luke 2:14.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.49,1:01:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They said:\N“Glory in the heights above to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.95,1:01:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and on earth peace among men of goodwill.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.49,1:01:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How appropriate for the angels to announce
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.12,1:01:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that at the birth\Nof the destined Prince of Peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.83,1:01:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be divine peace\Nfor those who have God’s goodwill!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.34,1:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But when will this become a reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.22,1:01:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn’t happen when Jesus was on earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.80,1:01:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and we certainly don’t see peace today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.68,1:01:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of peace, what do we see?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.81,1:01:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the nations that are locked\Nin hostilities and aggression
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.10,1:01:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in a competition for world dominance.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.85,1:02:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We see global violence and bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.15,1:02:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But please don’t lose heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.82,1:02:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we don’t see peace now\Ndoes not mean it’s not coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.07,1:02:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 9:6
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.99,1:02:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s not just wishful thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.33,1:02:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a promise from Almighty God,\Nand Jehovah cannot lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.13,1:02:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All his prophecies come true.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.21,1:02:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\Nlet’s read the last portion of verse 7
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.21,1:02:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in Isaiah chapter 9.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.59,1:02:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The last verse\N(the last portion of verse 7) says:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.01,1:02:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“The zeal of Jehovah of armies will do this.”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.73,1:02:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.73,1:02:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that Jehovah\Ndoes nothing in a half-hearted way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.69,1:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s zealous to bring peace, and he will.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.32,1:02:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be sure\Nthat whatever Jehovah promises,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.95,1:02:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,he will fully accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.16,1:02:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So how will peace come to the earth?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.62,1:02:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the Prince of Peace give us a clue?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.21,1:03:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.75,1:03:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the key to everlasting peace
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.79,1:03:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is on the lips of millions of people\Nthroughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.13,1:03:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They know it by heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.59,1:03:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s read it at Matthew 6:9, 10
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.85,1:03:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—Matthew 6:9.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.06,1:03:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful thought for us!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.06,1:03:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how everlasting peace\Nis going to come through.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.90,1:03:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on the fulfillment\Nof these verses.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.07,1:03:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.07,1:03:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must pray, then, this way:\N‘Our Father in the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.20,1:03:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,let your name [the name Jehovah]\Nbe sanctified.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.21,1:03:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The emphasis that we place\Non the name of God
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.08,1:03:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is not merely a matter\Nof religious knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.96,1:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone must know God’s name
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.09,1:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and treat it as something holy and respected.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.34,1:03:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be something sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.84,1:03:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be cleared of all the reproach\Nthat has been heaped upon it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.47,1:04:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the well-being\Nof the entire universe and its inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.44,1:04:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,depends upon the sanctification\Nof Jehovah’s name.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.11,1:04:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s look at verse 10:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.90,1:04:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let your Kingdom come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.70,1:04:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let your will take place,\Nas in heaven, also on earth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.66,1:04:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Kingdom\N—two words but so important.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.67,1:04:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Kingdom\Nis the most powerful government
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.26,1:04:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,humanity will ever see.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.51,1:04:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no nation or empire
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.51,1:04:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that can withstand\Nthe might of God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.77,1:04:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And any nation who thinks\Nthey can block the coming of God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.69,1:04:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is like an ant who plants itself firmly\Non the railroad track
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.69,1:04:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and with his hand raised defiantly\Nshouts to the oncoming locomotive:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.24,1:04:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Stop! You can’t run over me.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.20,1:05:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, God’s heavenly government has the power
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.45,1:05:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy all present-day violent regimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.29,1:05:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re like ants to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.08,1:05:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he will eliminate their ability
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.09,1:05:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to wage war, to foment conflict,\Nand to shed blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.92,1:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, Matthew 6:9, 10
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.93,1:05:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s that valuable and important\Nfor lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.76,1:05:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Kingdom is the only road\Nto lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.06,1:05:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And in his role as King,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.73,1:05:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 19:15 describes Jesus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.19,1:05:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as ‘striking the nations with an iron rod.’
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.15,1:05:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, Jehovah will give\Nthe command to his Son,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.87,1:05:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will destroy\Nall the things that disrupt peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.83,1:05:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Gone will be the terror\Nthat we have grown accustomed to living with
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.42,1:05:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,day in and day out.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.84,1:05:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what will happen next?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.38,1:05:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what will happen
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.76,1:05:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—Psalm 37:10, 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.22,1:06:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open our Bibles here\Nto Psalm 37:10, 11,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.68,1:06:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and just allow this prophecy to absorb
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.39,1:06:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and to thrill our minds and our hearts
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.40,1:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and give us a hope for the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.53,1:06:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 10 of Psalm 37:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.90,1:06:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just a little while longer,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.41,1:06:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the wicked will be no more\N[a little while longer];
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.24,1:06:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you will look at where they were,\Nand they will not be there.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.67,1:06:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just a little while longer.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.21,1:06:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just like children saying\Nto their parents
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.29,1:06:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when going on a trip\N“Are we there yet?”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.34,1:06:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the parents say\N“Just a little while longer.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.59,1:06:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings comfort to them,\Nand it’s the same with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.22,1:06:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So imagine that!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.22,1:06:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This means you go into the streets,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.35,1:06:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re looking for a wicked person,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.35,1:06:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will not be able to find even one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.69,1:06:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“The wicked will be no more.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.32,1:06:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the meek will possess the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.90,1:06:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we’re speaking about in verse 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.07,1:07:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that:\N“But the meek will possess the earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.41,1:07:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will find exquisite delight\Nin the abundance of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.25,1:07:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We love reading that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.67,1:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Men will be at peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.80,1:07:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be at peace with themselves,\Nwith their neighbors, with their God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.05,1:07:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that sound to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.55,1:07:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditate on that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.80,1:07:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see yourself there\Nin a peaceful new world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.64,1:07:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,where the only news to tune into
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.64,1:07:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is regarding who’s getting resurrected today
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.39,1:07:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or which new person you will be assigned\Nto teach about Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.57,1:07:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine the joy\Nof studying with a person,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.19,1:07:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not just from a different culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.32,1:07:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but from a different time period,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.70,1:07:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing things through their eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.45,1:07:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as they come to love Jehovah as you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.25,1:07:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, soon the Prince of Peace
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.79,1:07:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,will turn this world\Ninto one of sheer delight
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.84,1:07:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—no more borders,\Nno more threats, no more worries—
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.13,1:08:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,just an abundance of peace\Nwith your brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.43,1:08:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to be there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.89,1:08:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.10,1:08:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we show our loyal support\Nfor the Prince of Peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.11,1:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch the following video,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.36,1:08:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice the different ways\Nwe can do this right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.57,1:08:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am no part of the world.”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.16,1:08:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But is the world a part of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.71,1:08:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m pressured every day
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.72,1:08:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to get involved in political issues\Nthat affect me socially,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.02,1:08:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . environmentally,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.03,1:09:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and economically.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.87,1:09:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That pressure could rob me\Nof my peace of mind
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.04,1:09:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and influence how I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.30,1:09:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I could take sides in my heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.76,1:09:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,even if I’m not aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.23,1:09:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.10,1:09:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,will care for all of mankind’s concerns
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.76,1:10:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . by means of his Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.76,1:10:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,ruled by his Son, Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.23,1:10:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I show my support for him\Nin my prayers,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.48,1:10:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . in how I think and feel,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.04,1:10:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and by teaching others
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.12,1:10:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Kingdom will do for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.50,1:10:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there are millions
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.71,1:10:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of brothers and sisters\Nall over the world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.09,1:10:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . who loyally support\Nthe “Prince of Peace”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.22,1:10:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just like me, because I
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.89,1:10:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . I
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.77,1:10:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . I am no part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.48,1:11:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what takes away the peace\Nin the country where you live?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.03,1:11:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in your community?\Nin your town? in your society?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.45,1:11:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely,\Nit’s the hot-button social issues.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.83,1:11:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\Nhow our two brothers and sister
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.08,1:11:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,showed their loyal support\Nfor the Prince of Peace?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.42,1:11:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What issues affected them?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.42,1:11:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfair tax hikes, blatant injustice,\Na disregard of the environment
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.38,1:11:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—all things in themselves seemed\Nlike noble causes worthy to get involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.39,1:11:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How can they get away with this?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.43,1:11:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not right.\NWe should do something.’
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.18,1:11:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.23,1:11:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not have a literal sword in our hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.56,1:11:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but we all have our Peterlike moments.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.65,1:11:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we’re not careful,\Nissues that are close to our heart
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.28,1:11:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can charge our emotions\Nand we can lose our spiritual balance.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.58,1:11:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can help us\Nwhen we see things that are wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.58,1:11:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what the Prince of Peace\Nsaid to Peter
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.42,1:12:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in that highly charged moment:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.96,1:12:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“Return your sword to its place.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.21,1:12:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, this is not your fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.47,1:12:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.09,1:12:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We do something far better than fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.85,1:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We preach.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.47,1:12:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time that we share the Kingdom news,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.27,1:12:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we proclaim our support for Jesus’ rule.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.94,1:12:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s the thing:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.36,1:12:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If we truly believe\Nin the good news of the Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.99,1:12:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we will not do anything\Nthat hinders our ability to tell it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.24,1:12:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, it’s so important
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.87,1:12:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that if we truly believe\Nin the good news of the Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.91,1:12:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we will not do anything\Nthat hinders our ability to tell it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.92,1:12:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.00,1:12:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.30,1:12:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open up to Peter’s words himself
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.42,1:12:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Peter 2:12
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.76,1:12:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Peter 2:12.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.89,1:12:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter helps us here with why we need
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.35,1:13:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to maintain our conduct properly.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.19,1:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First Peter 2:12:
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.23,1:13:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Maintain your conduct fine\Namong the nations,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.78,1:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that when they accuse you\Nof being wrongdoers,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.91,1:13:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“they may be eyewitnesses\Nof your fine works
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.78,1:13:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and, as a result,\Nglorify God in the day of his inspection.”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.54,1:13:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So Peter had to learn this.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.04,1:13:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But do we see the connection?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.38,1:13:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our actions and words\Nare directly linked to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.42,1:13:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When people see us,\Nthey see a people that worships Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.10,1:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And when people hear us,\Nthey hear a people that worships Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.56,1:13:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how our freeness of speech\Nto speak about God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.44,1:13:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would be hindered if we were to voice\Na position for a political issue!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.44,1:13:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can happen so easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.70,1:13:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It can happen at work, at school,\Nwith relatives, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.12,1:13:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan sets the trap masterfully.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.95,1:13:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s just waiting.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.58,1:14:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If he could only make us\N“chop off the ear” of anything in this world
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.83,1:14:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that causes hurt and indignation in our heart
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.09,1:14:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or if he can hook our heartstrings\Nby getting us emotionally charged,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.68,1:14:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he can then step back and reel us in.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.35,1:14:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The new world, our hope for true peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.27,1:14:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all starts to fade into the background.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.56,1:14:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t give him that chance!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.40,1:14:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Be determined to do
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.40,1:14:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what Titus 3:1, 2 tells us.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.61,1:14:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.45,1:14:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—Titus chapter 3,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.83,1:14:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 1 and 2.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.83,1:14:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the Scriptural admonition:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.04,1:14:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue reminding them to be in subjection
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.42,1:14:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to be obedient\Nto governments and authorities,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.26,1:14:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“to be ready for every good work,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.68,1:14:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“to speak injuriously of no one,\Nnot to be quarrelsome,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.56,1:15:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but to be reasonable,\Ndisplaying all mildness toward all men.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.06,1:15:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Be in subjection
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.11,1:15:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and be obedient\Nto governments and authorities.’
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.57,1:15:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now let’s break that down.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.24,1:15:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In practical terms, what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.70,1:15:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to obey the laws of the land\Nand pay taxes,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.87,1:15:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to not speak negatively\Nabout the superior authorities,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.87,1:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be careful not to take sides\Non political issues
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.92,1:15:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,(not even in our hearts).
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.38,1:15:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember\Nthat expression from the video?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.51,1:15:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am no part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.63,1:15:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But is the world a part of me?”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.89,1:15:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,\Nwhen we find ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.89,1:15:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,between Caesar’s law and God’s law,\Nwe know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.10,1:15:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We apply Acts 5:29\Nand “obey God as ruler rather than men.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.98,1:15:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.98,1:15:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But like Jesus, who healed the ear\Nof the armed guard Malchus,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.24,1:15:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re determined to react with mildness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.65,1:16:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when provoked by an injustice\Nor cruelty in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.79,1:16:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.79,1:16:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the indescribable privilege\Nto honor the Prince of Peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.79,1:16:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And how reassuring it is to know\Nthat Jesus understands our feelings!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.80,1:16:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He understands our emotions\Nwhen we see things that we know are wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.80,1:16:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows these things hurt our heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.93,1:16:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We just want to make things right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.06,1:16:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember the critical lesson
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.56,1:16:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he taught his apostles\Nin the garden of Gethsemane:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.36,1:16:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not your fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.49,1:16:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, Jehovah, the King of Eternity,\Nand Jesus, the Prince of Peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.12,1:16:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are telling us:\N“This is our fight. Leave it in our hands.”
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.96,1:16:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, the prophecy at Isaiah 9:6, 7
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.92,1:16:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will be fulfilled completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.59,1:16:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime,\Nkeep preaching about the Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.93,1:16:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid saying or doing anything
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.93,1:17:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that suggests taking sides\Non a political issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.72,1:17:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t allow yourself to “chop off the ear”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.18,1:17:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the injustices and the causes of conflict\Nof this old world.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.27,1:17:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter tried that, but it didn’t work.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.69,1:17:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He learned a big lesson\Nthat day in the garden,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.69,1:17:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he never forgot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.70,1:17:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,May we never forget it either.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.16,1:17:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is the time to show\Nyour active and loyal support
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.70,1:17:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Prince of Peace
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.75,1:17:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as we echo Peter’s words at 2 Peter 3:14
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.75,1:17:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and “do [our] utmost to be found finally\Nby [Jehovah and the Prince of Peace]
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.67,1:17:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,spotless and unblemished and in peace.”
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.47,1:17:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Noumair,\Nfor strengthening our determination
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.85,1:17:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to give our undivided support
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.85,1:17:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to God’s appointed King, Christ Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.52,1:17:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us\Nto the final talk of today’s session.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.24,1:18:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus promised to give his followers peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.66,1:18:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the peace that Jesus gives\Nfar superior
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.66,1:18:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to any peace that this world promises?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.25,1:18:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we safeguard the gift of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.79,1:18:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus has given us?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.55,1:18:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Please follow along\Nas Brother Anthony Morris,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.05,1:18:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.05,1:18:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,delivers the talk,\N“Do Not Be Misled by Imitation Peace!”
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.94,1:18:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus taught us that Satan
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.94,1:18:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is “the father of the lie.”
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.82,1:18:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We recall that he deceived Eve,\Na perfect woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.41,1:18:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He lied about our precious Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.00,1:18:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you’re familiar (many of you)\Nwith Revelation chapter 12.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.29,1:18:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I invite you to find that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.50,1:19:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation chapter 12.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.55,1:19:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this chapter, verses 7 and 8,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.39,1:19:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it addressed the fact\Nthat “war broke out in heaven.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.81,1:19:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.81,1:19:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that after he’s kicked out of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.48,1:19:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in verse 9 we read:
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.27,1:19:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“So down the great dragon was hurled,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.94,1:19:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“the original serpent,\Nthe one called Devil and Satan,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.28,1:19:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“who is misleading\Nthe entire inhabited earth;
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.54,1:19:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“he was hurled down to the earth,\Nand his angels
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.96,1:19:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,were hurled down with him.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.87,1:19:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I read it that way specifically,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.88,1:19:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but what it doesn’t say is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.55,1:19:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,(in the middle part of verse 9):
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.84,1:19:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“Satan, who is [trying to mislead]
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.10,1:19:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire inhabited earth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.98,1:19:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}“is{\r}  misleading
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.36,1:19:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire inhabited earth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.73,1:20:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s crucial to understand\Nwhen we think about the theme of this talk,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.57,1:20:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be misled by imitation peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.20,1:20:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because as “the ruler of the world,”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.95,1:20:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s what he’s out to do—mislead.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.04,1:20:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it’s an interesting point\Nhere in 2 Corinthians chapter 11
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.38,1:20:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.80,1:20:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,how he goes about misleading,\Nor at least it’s addressed here
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.18,1:20:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve as a good warning for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.10,1:20:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And an interesting point with the revision
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.73,1:20:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.27,1:20:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(for those of you in the truth before 2013
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.40,1:20:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was revised, you’ll remember this)
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.66,1:20:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in verse 14 of 2 Corinthians chapter 11:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.87,1:20:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“And no wonder,\Nfor Satan himself keeps disguising himself
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.71,1:20:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as an angel of light.”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.17,1:21:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.13,1:21:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,used to say before the revision
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.88,1:21:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“[transforms] himself\Ninto an angel of light.”
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.26,1:21:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the very English word “metamorphosis,”
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.06,1:21:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like for a caterpillar transforming\Ninto a beautiful butterfly,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.06,1:21:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s where it comes from,\Nthe Greek language.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.32,1:21:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that word was not in verse 14.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.32,1:21:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because Satan can’t transform himself
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.20,1:21:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,into “an angel of light”\N(so it’s an improved translation),
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.75,1:21:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but he does disguise.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.25,1:21:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s a masquerader.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.67,1:21:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And he does that with the subject of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.67,1:21:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,His world offers a sort of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.93,1:21:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.68,1:21:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jesus is distinguished,\Nthough, with the peace that he gives.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.02,1:21:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’ll follow along here
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.23,1:22:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in John chapter 14,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.78,1:22:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he himself explains it to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.11,1:22:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we treasure the Gospel accounts,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.57,1:22:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 27: “I leave you peace;
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.95,1:22:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“I give you my peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.71,1:22:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“I do not give it to you\Nthe way the world gives it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.46,1:22:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let your hearts be troubled\Nnor let them shrink out of fear.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.46,1:22:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus gives us his peace, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.09,1:22:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the peace that Jesus gives us,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.72,1:22:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s this inner calm once you know\Nthe truth and Jesus gives us the peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.73,1:22:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have this confidence that he loves us\Nand Jehovah loves us,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.73,1:22:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we enjoy a good,\Npeaceful relationship with them
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.44,1:22:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.57,1:22:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we look forward to the Kingdom\Nremoving all war and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.41,1:22:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a point to make here:
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.41,1:23:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan wants us to trade
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.54,1:23:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace that Jesus gives
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.92,1:23:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for his imitation peace
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.34,1:23:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that he has advertised in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.43,1:23:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this talk,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.93,1:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we will consider\Nthree forms of imitation peace
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.98,1:23:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and why the peace\Nthat Jesus gives is superior.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.48,1:23:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one has to do with material things
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.61,1:23:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—how they’ll not bring true peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.62,1:23:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And to help us with that,\Nturn to Matthew chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.12,1:23:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll be referring to this chapter
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.50,1:23:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout this particular talk\Nabout not being misled by imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.55,1:23:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one\Nis connected with material things
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.05,1:23:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—how they don’t bring true peace—
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.05,1:23:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the example Jesus sets forth here.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.60,1:23:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So in Matthew chapter 4:
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.43,1:23:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jesus was led by the spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.85,1:24:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“up into the wilderness\Nto be tempted by the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.65,1:24:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“After he had fasted\Nfor 40 days and 40 nights,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.11,1:24:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“he felt hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.15,1:24:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the Tempter approached and said to him:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.24,1:24:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If you are a son of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.70,1:24:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,tell these stones to become loaves of bread.’
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.95,1:24:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“But he answered: ‘It is written:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.54,1:24:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“Man must live, not on bread alone,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.88,1:24:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but on every word that comes\Nfrom Jehovah’s mouth.”’”
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.51,1:24:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful rebuttal?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.09,1:24:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jesus refused to trade
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.01,1:24:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,his peace for material things\N(in this case, bread),
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.14,1:24:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,even though he was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.10,1:24:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So serving Jehovah was more important to him
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.07,1:24:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,than material things, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.82,1:24:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world, they have this thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.11,1:24:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, you need
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.62,1:24:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain amount of money to retire,’
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.33,1:25:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re constantly\Nfocused on material things
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.33,1:25:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—not Jesus, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.04,1:25:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s superior peace from Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.72,1:25:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s only temporary anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.55,1:25:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the material benefits that people seek
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.93,1:25:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and pursue throughout their lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.14,1:25:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can enjoy true contentment
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.65,1:25:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah God is going to care for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.73,1:25:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that many have\Npersonal experiences to prove that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.74,1:25:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the following video,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.28,1:25:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,see what a brother learned\Nabout the so-called peace
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.54,1:25:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world promises.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.71,1:25:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As a family, we were doing\Nvery well spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.30,1:25:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We did family worship, went preaching,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.18,1:25:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and went to the meetings together.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.22,1:26:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,After some time, we began
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.89,1:26:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to encounter financial problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.39,1:26:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, we did not even have money\Nto buy food
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.56,1:26:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for each day.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.57,1:26:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people in our area\Nwere going to South Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.11,1:26:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide basic needs for their families.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.24,1:26:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided to go as well,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.37,1:26:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving behind my wife\Nto take care of our seven children.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.96,1:26:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This affected me spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.97,1:26:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because I did not know the language,\NI was unable to preach,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.80,1:26:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did not benefit from the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.31,1:26:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Being so far from my family
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.39,1:26:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,caused me to neglect\Nmy responsibility as a family head.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.15,1:26:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, my family grew weak spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.53,1:26:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all missed each other very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.07,1:27:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I had made\Na wrong decision going abroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.03,1:27:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My conscience started to trouble me greatly.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.79,1:27:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I remembered the example of Baruch
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.12,1:27:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,found at Jeremiah 45:5.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.84,1:27:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Baruch may have wanted\Nto pursue material riches as I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.05,1:27:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was helped, he returned.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.18,1:27:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided then to put Jehovah in first place
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.85,1:27:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of searching for material things.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.98,1:27:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started to make changes to go home
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.11,1:27:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and help my family spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.44,1:27:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When I left South Africa\Nand reached the border of Malawi
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.95,1:27:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,(after leaving my family\Nfor about six months),
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.28,1:27:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt great happiness in my heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.62,1:27:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am still happy till now.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.17,1:27:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying the Bible has helped me.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.00,1:27:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We still encounter financial problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.55,1:27:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but I remember that in Satan’s world,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.55,1:28:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nowhere we can go\Nand have no problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.39,1:28:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I serve as an elder.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.56,1:28:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My family is progressing spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.73,1:28:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this makes me very happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.90,1:28:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because my relationship\Nwith Jehovah is strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.07,1:28:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he learned a hard lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.41,1:28:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes to South Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.71,1:28:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—meetings interrupted and no field service.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.13,1:28:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he remembers Baruch,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.09,1:28:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,secretary for Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.97,1:28:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And he returns to be with his family,\Nputting the Kingdom first,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.85,1:28:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we appreciate him\Nbeing truthful and sharing that experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.35,1:28:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s imitation peace,\Ngoing after material things.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.27,1:28:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this next one, it’s quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.53,1:29:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.53,1:29:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because there may be some\Nlistening who need this counsel.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.08,1:29:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan’s world says that we
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.00,1:29:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,can ignore Bible standards
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.29,1:29:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we might need\Nto ignore some of them to gain peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.29,1:29:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are two examples\Nthat we’re going to analyze in this talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.97,1:29:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A person may reason\Nthat marrying an unbeliever
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.85,1:29:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or obtaining an unscriptural divorce
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.02,1:29:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,will make life easier.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.85,1:29:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And they start reasoning this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.27,1:29:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I just want to get married,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.48,1:29:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s an unbeliever,\Nbut he’s a nice person.’
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.61,1:29:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Things like that go on\Nwith the treacherous heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.62,1:29:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we go to the example\Nof our Lord and Master, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.45,1:29:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to read verses 5-7 of Matthew 4:
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.84,1:30:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then the Devil took him\Nalong into the holy city,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.72,1:30:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he stationed him\Non the battlement of the temple
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.14,1:30:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“and said to him:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.26,1:30:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If you are a son of God,\Nthrow yourself down,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.27,1:30:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for it is written:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.31,1:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“He will give his angels\Na command concerning you,” 
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.69,1:30:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and, “They will carry you on their hands,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.44,1:30:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that you may not strike\Nyour foot against a stone.”’
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.03,1:30:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus said to him: ‘Again, it is written:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.37,1:30:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must not put Jehovah\Nyour God to the test.”’”
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.12,1:30:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jesus made that very clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.79,1:30:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going to be obedient to his Father
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.50,1:30:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and wasn’t going to worry about being testy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.88,1:30:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with such an experience\Nas the Devil proposed there.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.76,1:30:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So obedience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.35,1:30:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jesus twice (in a moment we’ll read\Nanother one) said: “It is written.”
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.98,1:31:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He sticks with the Scriptures\N—Jehovah’s thinking—
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.11,1:31:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and he refused to disobey Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.99,1:31:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here’s the question,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.08,1:31:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the peace that Jesus gives
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.33,1:31:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,superior to the pursuit
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.83,1:31:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of unscriptural solutions to our problems?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.59,1:31:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let that sink in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.63,1:31:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the peace that Jesus gives
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.34,1:31:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,superior to the pursuit
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.59,1:31:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of unscriptural solutions to our problems?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.64,1:31:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, marrying an unbeliever
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.81,1:31:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—that will likely bring\N(and it has happened time after time)
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.90,1:31:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that person greater pain
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.07,1:31:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than the longing\Nthey felt when they were single.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.28,1:31:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve personally seen that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.28,1:31:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all too many times in various congregations
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.29,1:31:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’ve had the privilege to serve in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.54,1:32:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the other one\Nis an unscriptural divorce.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.59,1:32:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It often leads to immoral conduct.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.80,1:32:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly leads to a troubled conscience,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.05,1:32:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,emotional damage\Nand, of course, a loss of privileges.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.31,1:32:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is very important to keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.52,1:32:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that with two imperfect individuals
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.15,1:32:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,married to each other,\Nwell, there are going to be difficulties
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.20,1:32:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are going to be challenges.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.20,1:32:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But stop and think about this:
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.79,1:32:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re having difficulties,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.25,1:32:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t forget that marriage
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.21,1:32:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is a sacred arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.75,1:32:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The world totally has forgotten that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.59,1:32:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah will strengthen
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.80,1:32:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,both to make a success.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.68,1:32:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to keep that in mind:\NJehovah will strengthen and help
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.14,1:33:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can succeed\Nbecause this is his sacred arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.44,1:33:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Devil has been attacking\Nthe family arrangement
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.15,1:33:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,all through the last days of this system,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.78,1:33:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s intensifying it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.87,1:33:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as he gets closer\Nto being thrown into the abyss.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.00,1:33:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the following video,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.58,1:33:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the results\Nof pursuing imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.92,1:33:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Newly married life came with a lot
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.97,1:33:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of unexpected challenges.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.26,1:33:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You dream about the way\Nyour marriage will go,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.64,1:33:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but then the reality is quite different.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.23,1:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All we ever did was argue,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.31,1:33:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or we wouldn’t speak to one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.15,1:33:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We never ever went to the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.86,1:33:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We just didn’t want to bother them.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.40,1:33:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We just felt, you know,\Nwe needed to figure it out ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.54,1:33:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided that if the house sold,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.75,1:34:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then we would separate.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.42,1:34:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The separation wasn’t a good thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.42,1:34:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because in some respects\Nit made things worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.76,1:34:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It did have an impact on the boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.26,1:34:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They started acting out.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.35,1:34:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They got into some trouble\Nwith the police one time.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.27,1:34:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a loneliness\Nbecause you’ve gotten married,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.32,1:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you don’t have that,\Nand you’re by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.32,1:34:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same old routine\Nwent on where you’re
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.28,1:34:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cooking and cleaning\Nand doing laundry and working.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.37,1:34:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt sick to my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.29,1:34:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a hard time getting up every morning\Nand facing the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.46,1:34:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, I felt that I needed
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.83,1:34:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to have the elders help out a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.42,1:34:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I did pray for Jehovah’s help to direct me,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.51,1:34:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kept wondering\Nwhy Jehovah wasn’t really
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.89,1:34:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,answering my prayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.10,1:35:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I kind of realize now\Nthat it was because we were separated.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.10,1:35:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The expectations of the separation\Nwere not at all what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.57,1:35:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I reflected on the marriage vows.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.90,1:35:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things I thought about
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.07,1:35:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was a sister in our congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.41,1:35:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She was married to an unbeliever,\Nand then she learned the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.87,1:35:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was so violent.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.16,1:35:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He would beat her; he would burn her books;\Nhe would burn her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.79,1:35:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not allow her children\Nto attend the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.71,1:35:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought about the problems\Nthat Darrel and I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.59,1:35:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought:\N‘Well, Darrel is a kind person.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.80,1:35:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s never done that.’
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.05,1:35:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought:
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.51,1:35:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You know, this is something
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.10,1:35:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that we need to really work on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.43,1:35:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We need to really put forth the effort
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.98,1:35:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to start applying Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.65,1:35:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to put Jehovah first in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.61,1:35:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can bring our marriage\Nback in union with Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.49,1:35:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that it wasn’t what I wanted,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.11,1:35:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was what Jehovah wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.74,1:36:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.96,1:36:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wasn’t going to bless us\Nunless we got back together.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.96,1:36:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When we got back together,\Nour marriage was still a work in progress.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.59,1:36:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t have\Na perfect marriage in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.59,1:36:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can sure make it better\Nwhen you put Jehovah first.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.35,1:36:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We enjoyed the feelings\Nwe had toward each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.68,1:36:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt closer to Debbie.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.44,1:36:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Debbie and I\Nhave been married now for 48 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.69,1:36:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Separation does not make\Nanything better at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.90,1:36:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you even have an inkling of love\Nfor one another,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.11,1:36:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to work on that,\Nand you want to make it bloom
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.62,1:36:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,so that Jehovah can bless it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.62,1:36:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The blessings have been endless.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.66,1:36:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Our children are all doing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.66,1:36:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.29,1:36:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said:\N“Taste and see that [He] is good.”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.59,1:36:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’ve got to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.64,1:37:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We really appreciated this couple sharing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.76,1:37:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,their experience with the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.14,1:37:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He learned, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.56,1:37:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They were always arguing,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.56,1:37:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s all they\Ndid was argue, argue, argue.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.28,1:37:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It affected their children.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.11,1:37:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They decided to separate\Nand finally have peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.74,1:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I don’t have to be around her,’\Nor ‘I don’t have to be around him.’
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.00,1:37:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he realized\Nhis relationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.96,1:37:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was being interfered with here,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.75,1:37:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and he went to the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.67,1:37:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,His prayers were affected.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.67,1:37:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The things he noticed\N—he was honest about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.43,1:37:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And our precious sister\Nwas so nice to honestly explain.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.18,1:37:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She said what she learned\Nwas that ‘this is not about me;
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.73,1:37:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s about Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.15,1:37:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When you finally come to that realization,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.48,1:37:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will strengthen you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.69,1:38:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy peace with your marriage partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.78,1:38:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next one, I never tire of speaking
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.29,1:38:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,about these particular couple of verses
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.29,1:38:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or reading about it or hearing\Nanother brother give a talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.96,1:38:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See, here’s what’s coming soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.43,1:38:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn with me to 1 Thessalonians chapter 5.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.18,1:38:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of you are going, ‘Oh, yeah, I know
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.93,1:38:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what he’s going to read about.’
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.35,1:38:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is one of the prophecies
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.56,1:38:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that is yet to be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.82,1:38:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s just invigorating
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.15,1:38:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to know that soon\Nhere’s what’s going to happen
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.57,1:38:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Thessalonians chapter 5,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.83,1:38:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 2 and 3:
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.04,1:38:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For you yourselves know very well
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.00,1:38:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“that Jehovah’s day\Nis coming exactly as a thief in the night.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.26,1:39:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whenever it is that they are saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.80,1:39:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Peace and security!’
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.30,1:39:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“then sudden destruction\Nis to be instantly on them,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.18,1:39:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“just like birth pains on a pregnant woman,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.15,1:39:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will by no means escape.”
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.69,1:39:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, see, “Jehovah’s day”
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.74,1:39:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—this has to do with the day\Nof the outbreak of the great tribulation
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.37,1:39:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when Babylon the Great is destroyed
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.58,1:39:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and Armageddon finishes it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.92,1:39:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In this context, that’s “Jehovah’s day.”
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.13,1:39:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens before then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.13,1:39:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is this proclamation, “peace and security!”
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.55,1:39:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Will religious leaders be involved?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.26,1:39:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they’re part of Satan’s system;\Nthat’s very possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.10,1:39:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll have to wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.35,1:39:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be one announcement\Nor a series of announcements?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.69,1:39:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That we don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.69,1:39:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.69,1:40:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who are staying close to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.53,1:40:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoying the peace\Nfrom him and his Son, Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.28,1:40:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,will not be deceived
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.79,1:40:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by this imitation proclamation of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.87,1:40:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.42,1:40:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, back in Matthew chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.09,1:40:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to see how Jesus handled
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.80,1:40:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this type of test from the Devil
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.55,1:40:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we learn from it here
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.93,1:40:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in verses 8-11 of Matthew chapter 4.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.10,1:40:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Again the Devil took him [in verse 8]
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.02,1:40:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“along to an unusually high mountain
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.49,1:40:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“and showed him all the kingdoms\Nof the world and their glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.03,1:40:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“And he said to him:
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.41,1:40:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘All these things I will give you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.45,1:40:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“if you fall down\Nand do an act of worship to me.’
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.00,1:41:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jesus said to him [without hesitation]:
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.42,1:41:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Go away, Satan!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.88,1:41:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For it is written:\N“It is Jehovah your God you must worship,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.51,1:41:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is to him alone\Nyou must render sacred service.”’
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.10,1:41:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then the Devil left him,\Nand look! angels came
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.11,1:41:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and began to minister to him.”
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.90,1:41:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Right away, a third time: “It is written.”
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.49,1:41:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was having nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.87,1:41:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with this offer of the kingdoms\N—this imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.04,1:41:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You’ll have all the glory and rule.’
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.00,1:41:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s always boggled my mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.21,1:41:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that this one who knew
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.63,1:41:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus in his prehuman existence
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.63,1:41:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would have the audacity to try to get Jesus\Nto bow down and worship him.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.60,1:41:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows you that he’s obviously insane.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.02,1:42:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he wouldn’t allow it either
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.07,1:42:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when they tried to make him an earthly king.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.48,1:42:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus wasn’t having any part of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.03,1:42:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They were thinking he could bring them peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.28,1:42:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus said there’s no peace\Nexcept by Jehovah’s way.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.16,1:42:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And the peace from God’s Kingdom\Nis so superior
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.58,1:42:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to anything they could try to come up with\N—their imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.30,1:42:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s why.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.42,1:42:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about this:
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.97,1:42:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus will remove the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.06,1:42:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus will remove human rulership.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.77,1:42:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus will remove sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.44,1:42:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So the earth’s peace\Nwill never again be disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.07,1:42:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I appreciate very much\Nthat he’s going to get rid of all problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.83,1:42:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and that includes undoing all causes of pain
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.29,1:42:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—and not just physical pain,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.33,1:43:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,emotional pain as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.63,1:43:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s wonderful to look forward to that time
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.01,1:43:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with that beautiful peace
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.26,1:43:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from our precious Father,\NJehovah, and his Son, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.72,1:43:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the following video,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.81,1:43:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,see what convinced this sister
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.14,1:43:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not to believe the world’s promises of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.53,1:43:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My father always taught me\Nthat we needed God in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.57,1:43:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in order for there to be peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.33,1:43:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And he always wanted to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.41,1:43:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Can Christians go to war?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.71,1:43:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How is this consistent\Nwith the Gospel of Jesus Christ?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.46,1:43:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the pastor could never give us an answer,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.97,1:43:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I thought I’d have to look\Nto politics to find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.43,1:43:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of peace movements\Nwere being formed at that time,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.89,1:43:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so I joined one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.73,1:44:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided where\Nthe protest marches would be
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.61,1:44:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and which pamphlets we would use.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.28,1:44:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the protests were over,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.86,1:44:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone was so excited
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.24,1:44:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all started applauding
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.54,1:44:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and cheering for the leaders.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.58,1:44:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought:\N‘That’s not what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.04,1:44:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I don’t want to honor people.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.34,1:44:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I want to have world peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.55,1:44:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that still hasn’t happened yet.’
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.47,1:44:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I started to feel very alone,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.64,1:44:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and it made me feel unsafe in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.64,1:44:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,With no peace in sight,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.65,1:44:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought,\N‘What is the purpose of life?’
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.69,1:44:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,While visiting friends for coffee,\NI saw a man I’d never met before.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.49,1:44:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends told me he wanted\Nto talk to us about the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.91,1:45:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I asked him:
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.71,1:45:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sir, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.67,1:45:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Can Christians join the military?”
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.75,1:45:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the man said,\N“No, that’s not allowed
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.38,1:45:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Bible says\Nyou should ‘love your [enemy].’”
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.14,1:45:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me think\Nabout what my father always said
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.39,1:45:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we need God to bring peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.48,1:45:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a really nice lady came to my door,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.48,1:45:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and she had an orange book in her hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.94,1:45:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it said:\N{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}True Peace and Security.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.70,1:45:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading it, I thought:
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.83,1:45:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This is it!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.87,1:45:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the organization\Nthat truly wants peace.’
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.96,1:45:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to those involved\Nin the peace movement.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.51,1:45:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I told them that I believe\Nthat God will change this world
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.51,1:45:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,into a beautiful earth\Nwhere there’ll be true peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.35,1:46:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They all looked at me\Nlike I had lost my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.02,1:46:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so happy with my new life.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.69,1:46:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was part of a family
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.52,1:46:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who truly cared about one another
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.57,1:46:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and really wanted peace with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.45,1:46:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 14:7 had a major impact on my life
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.62,1:46:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because there God promises
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.83,1:46:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a calm and peaceful world.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.88,1:46:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn’t that nice how she learned?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.43,1:46:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She’d looked to politics and protests\Nfor world peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.02,1:46:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, she was sincere.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.56,1:46:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But she learned that’s all imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.40,1:46:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,True peace and security\Ncomes from Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.53,1:47:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So wrapping it up with these\Nthree different types
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.20,1:47:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of imitation peace\Nthat we’ve emphasized,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.83,1:47:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to encourage you\Nin these last minutes
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.50,1:47:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to safeguard the peace\Nthat Jesus has given you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.30,1:47:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In John chapter 14
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.68,1:47:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,(you know this,\Nbut I want you to really focus
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.93,1:47:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on a particular point), in verse 6:
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.02,1:47:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus said to him:
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.02,1:47:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I am the way and the truth and the life.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.61,1:47:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No one comes to the Father\Nexcept through me.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.62,1:47:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.91,1:47:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly we want to emphasize\NJesus is “the truth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.84,1:47:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We can trust all of his promises.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.17,1:47:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He is “the truth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.88,1:48:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to give us peace\N—already has—
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.93,1:48:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and will to a greater extent in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.10,1:48:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our Master is “the truth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.56,1:48:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And he gave the early Christians that peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.36,1:48:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that they were able to deal\Nwith are just mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.65,1:48:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read the apostle Paul’s experiences\Nand Peter’s and others’
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.66,1:48:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—the persecution they endured—\Nthey did it,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.24,1:48:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,enduring with joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.08,1:48:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.50,1:48:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be\Na supernatural provision of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.50,1:48:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And just remember,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.76,1:48:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus will likewise give you\Nthe peace you need now
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.51,1:48:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep doing Jehovah’s will\Nand to make Him happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.52,1:48:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, please,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.90,1:48:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,safeguard the gift of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.19,1:48:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus has given you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.40,1:48:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan uses this world
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.49,1:49:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to offer you promises of imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.20,1:49:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be misled!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.00,1:49:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, rather, “Let the peace of the Christ\Nrule in your hearts.”
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.58,1:49:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“And show yourselves thankful.”
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.00,1:49:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, through his Son,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.00,1:49:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will bless us all with peace forever!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.64,1:49:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Morris,\Nfor strengthening our trust in Jesus’ promise
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.56,1:49:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to give us peace now and during the events\Nthat will shortly take place.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.94,1:49:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The second session of our convention\Nhas truly helped us 
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.40,1:49:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how Jehovah blesses us with peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.28,1:49:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we look forward to\Nin the next session?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.33,1:49:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture theme will be\Nfrom 2 Peter 3:14:
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.96,1:49:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be found . . . spotless and unblemished\Nand in peace.”
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.42,1:49:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The program will begin with a symposium\Nthat will help prepare us
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.51,1:50:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to share the “good news of peace”\Nat every opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.18,1:50:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones can look forward\Nto a special talk just for them
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.56,1:50:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,given by a member of the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.65,1:50:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll also see how brothers and sisters\Nare maintaining their peace
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.94,1:50:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even when suffering from illness,\Neconomic problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.78,1:50:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,natural disasters, and other difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.33,1:50:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, our next session\Nincludes the baptism talk,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.04,1:50:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,after which those who have been approved
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.46,1:50:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,will be baptized locally.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.29,1:50:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We have much to look forward to!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.63,1:50:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude today’s session,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.63,1:50:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s sing song number 112, entitled
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.05,1:50:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah, God of Peace.”
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.56,1:50:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that’s song number 112.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.23,1:50:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After the song concludes,\Nyou may have your own closing prayer.
